# Painting prompt template -- the prompt sent to Gemini's image model.
#
# Lines starting with '#' are comments and are ignored. Blank lines are
# preserved (they separate sections of the prompt).
#
# Placeholders -- these get filled in automatically each day:
#   {art_style}       the art style picked for today (e.g. "Hokusai woodblock")
#   {pet_description} the contents of the petDescription file
#   {environment}     the setting that Gemini invented for today
#   {activity}        what the pet is doing today
#   {mood}            two or three mood words
#   {palette}         a short colour-palette description
#
# Edit freely. To restore the default, check git history for this file.

{art_style} painting of a domestic pet.

The pet (keep faithful to this exact description):
{pet_description}

Setting: {environment}
The pet is: {activity}
Mood: {mood}.
Colour palette: {palette}.

Depiction: render the pet as a real painting in the chosen medium -- not
cartoonish and not photorealistic. Where the medium has visible mark-making
(oil, gouache, watercolour, pastel, ink), let the brushwork and texture of
the medium show clearly. The pet should look painted, not posed for a camera.

Composition: gallery-quality, 16:9 landscape orientation, the pet as the clear
focal point, balanced negative space. No text, no captions, no signatures,
no watermark, no border or frame within the image.
